# Editor / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Windows reserved device names — `nul` / `con` / `prn` / `aux` can be
# created as stray 0-byte files by an accidental `> nul` redirect from a
# non-cmd shell (git-bash / wsl treat `nul` as a literal filename). They
# cannot be deleted with plain `rm`; ignore them so they never get tracked.
nul
con
prn
aux
